  }, {
    "href": "https://readwise.io/to_kindle?action=open&asin=B06WVYW33Y&location=1509"
  }), "Location\xA01509"), ")"), mdx("p", null, "It is so much easier to develop an interesting text from a lively discussion with a lot of pros and cons than from a collection of one-sided notes and seemingly fitting quotes. In fact, it is almost impossible to write anything interesting and worth publishing (and therefore motivating) if it is based on nothing else than an idea we were able to come up with up front before elaborating on the problem. (", mdx("a", _extends({
