  }, {
    "href": "https://readwise.io/to_kindle?action=open&asin=B06WVYW33Y&location=1748"
  }), "Location\xA01748"), ")"), mdx("p", null, "Concluding the discussions in this book, Levy writes: \u201CIn any case, no matter how internal processes are implemented, insofar as thinkers are genuinely concerned with what enables human beings to perform the spectacular intellectual feats exhibited in science and other areas of systematic enquiry, as well as in the arts, they need to understand the extent to which the mind is reliant upon external scaffolding.\u201D (", mdx("a", _extends({
