  }, {
    "href": "https://readwise.io/to_kindle?action=open&asin=B06WVYW33Y&location=2022"
  }), "Location\xA02022"), ")"), mdx("p", null, "Good keywords are usually not already mentioned as words in the note. Assume I have the note \u201CA sudden increase of ad-hoc theories is for Kuhn a sign that a normal-science phase might be in crisis (Kuhn 1967, 96).\u201D A fitting keyword might be \u201Cparadigm change,\u201D but that phrase is not in the note and therefore would not be suggested by the program. Assigning keywords is much more than just a bureaucratic act. (", mdx("a", _extends({
