  }, {
    "href": "https://readwise.io/to_kindle?action=open&asin=B06WVYW33Y&location=2140"
  }), "Location\xA02140"), ")"), mdx("p", null, "You are less prone to make this error in judgement if you know about it (Rasin 2014). You are welcome."), mdx("h3", null, "New highlights added November 5th, 2020 at 7:32 PM"), mdx("p", null, "A truly wise person is not someone who knows everything, but someone who is able to make sense of things by drawing from an extended resource of interpretation schemes. This stands in harsh contrast to the common but not-so-wise belief that we need to learn from experience. It is much better to learn from the experiences of others \u2013 especially when this experience is reflected on and turned into versatile \u201Cmental models\u201D that can be used in different situations. (", mdx("a", _extends({
